ons":56},"Letters are deeply v-cut, somewhat elongated, and showing some tendency towards curvature in e.g. the M. Minial use of serifs. Lunate omega, but rectilinear epsilon and sigma. Alpha with broken bar; mu with four full-length, slanting strokes; kappa with short ams; omicron ovoid but full height; epsilon tall and thin, all bars of equal length; zeta an equal length Z. Use of interpunct to mark off the names, and hedera around the numeral.",[57,63,67,72],{"type":58,"l":59,"from":60,"to":60,"h":61,"unit":62},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","29-38","mm",{"type":58,"l":64,"from":65,"to":65,"h":66,"unit":62},"Line 2","line2","25-30",{"type":58,"l":68,"from":69,"to":70,"h":71,"unit":62},"Line 3-5","line3","line5","30-34",{"type":73,"l":74,"from":60,"to":65,"unit":62},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2",{"_":76,"notBefore":77,"notAfter":78,"precision":79},"1st — 3rd century CE",1,300,"low",[81,85],{"_":82,"type":83,"ref":84},"Centuripae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462153",{"_":86,"type":87,"ref":88},"Centuripe","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525032",[90],[91,92],37.62336,14.74049,[],{"_":95,"type":96,"subtype":97,"notAfter":98,"geo":18},"Exact details not recorded, found in Centuripe prior to 1906, and purchased for the Siracusa museum by Paolo Orsi, 1906-01-24; currently in storage, Magazzino B, cassette 4.","observed","discovered","1906",[100,107,109,114],{"n":101,"url":102,"height":103,"width":104,"desc":105,"surfaceType":106},"screen","ISic003424_tiled.tif","2454px","3220px","Photo J. Prag, 2014-09-10, by permission of Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi","front",{"n":101,"url":108,"height":103,"width":104,"desc":105,"surfaceType":106},"ISic003424.jpg",{"n":101,"url":110,"height":111,"width":112,"desc":105,"surfaceType":113},"ISic003424_rear_tiled.tif","2395px","3131px","rear",{"n":101,"url":115,"height":111,"width":112,"desc":105,"surfaceType":113},"ISic003424_rear.jpg","Italy","Sicily","Siracusa",{"_":120,"role":121,"ref":122,"m